,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":56307,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/programming-help-for-tracking-april-tags-with-limelight/453574/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3303031,"name":"icemannie","username":"icemannie","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/bc79bd/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-06T14:42:20.885Z","cooked":"<p>You need a WPILIB swerve drive pose estimator which tracks the robot pose on the field using wheel encoders and gyro. It has an addVisionMeasurement method which allows Limelight to correct the pose from AprilTag data.</p>
<p>See this    <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/swerve-drive-pose-estimator-and-add-vision-measurement-using-limelight-is-very-jittery/453306">Swerve Drive Pose Estimator and Add Vision Measurement using Limelight is very jittery - Technical - Chief Delphi</a>and other threads - search “swerve drive pose estimator” for more complete information. Also be aware of the final posts in this thread<br>
