03159,"name":"Tyson Whelan","username":"Tyson453","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e56c9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-06T17:00:12.801Z","cooked":"<p>Here is a link to how my team approaches retrieving and processing Limelight data for reference: <a href="https://github.com/frc2357/FRC-2024/blob/main/robotbase/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Limelight.java" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">FRC-2024/robotbase/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Limelight.java at main · frc2357/FRC-2024 · GitHub</a></p>
<p>I didn’t make it and I’ve never needed to understand how it all worked, but I can try to help answer any questions you have. I’m also working on a DriveToApriltagCommand that uses the limelight output if you’d like to see that as a reference.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-02-06T17:01:39.990Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":53,"reads":312,"readers_count":311,"score":342.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":453574,"topic_slug":"programming-help-for-tracking-april-tags-with-limelight","display_username":"Tyson Whelan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/frc2357/FRC-2024/blob/main/robotbase/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/Limelight.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":273}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51010,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2357 Drive Coach"},"post_url":"/t/programming-help-for-tracking-april-tags-with-limelight/453574/3","custom_user_title":"2357 Drive Coach","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3303259,"name":"Sean B","username":"Phlogiston","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/phlogiston/{size}/180763_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-06T18:13:26.060Z","cooked":"<p>depending on what your goal is, you might not have to use a pose estimator. If you just want to drive to a fixed position, first make sure 3d tracking is enabled on the limelight - see <a href="https://docs.limelightvision.io/docs/docs-limelight/pipeline-apriltag/apriltag-3d" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">3D AprilTags | Limelight Documentation</a>. Then, the simplest way to drive to a point is to use the targetpose_cameraspace NetworkTables field, which will give you the pose of the tag relative to the camera. You can directly offset the X/Y/Rotation and feed it into a <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller to get you to your point of interest.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-02-06T18:13:26.060Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":266,"readers_count":265,"score":138.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":453574,"topic_slug":"programming-help-for-tracking-april-tags-with-limelight","display_username":"Sean B","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.limelightvision.io/docs/docs-limelight/pipeline-apriltag/apriltag-3d","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"3D AprilTags | Limelight Documentation","clicks":72}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44845,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Lone Coder"},"post_url":"/t/programming-help-for-tracking-april-tags-with-limelight/453574/4","custom_user_title":"Lone Coder","reactions":[{"id":"heart",